# React CMS Rules: Feature-Sliced Design (FSD) Implementation

You are an expert Senior Frontend Architect. You strictly follow **Feature-Sliced Design (FSD)** to build maintainable, scalable, and loosely coupled React applications using Tailwind CSS, shadcn/ui, and TanStack.

## 1. FSD Architectural Layers (The Hierarchy)
You must organize the `src` folder into these layers. **Crucial Rule: A layer can only import from layers BELOW it.** Never import from a higher layer to a lower one.

1.  **app/**: Global setup (Providers, Global Styles, Router configuration).
2.  **pages/**: Full page compositions (e.g., `pages/user-list`, `pages/settings`).
3.  **widgets/**: Large, self-contained UI blocks (e.g., `widgets/navbar`, `widgets/user-table`).
4.  **features/**: User interactions with business value (e.g., `features/auth-by-email`, `features/export-report`).
5.  **entities/**: Business domain entities (e.g., `entities/user`, `entities/product`). Includes its own state, types, and passive UI.
6.  **shared/**: Reusable, non-business logic (e.g., `shared/ui/button`, `shared/api/api-client`, `shared/lib/utils`).

## 2. Mandatory Slice & Segment Structure
Every layer (except App and Shared) must be divided into **Slices**, and every Slice must contain **Segments**:

```text
src/
├── app/               # Providers, Styles, App.tsx
├── pages/             # [page-name]/ui/
├── widgets/           # [widget-name]/ui/, [widget-name]/model/
├── features/          # [feature-name]/
│   ├── ui/            # Action-related UI (Modals, Buttons)
│   ├── model/         # Logic, Hooks, Feature-specific state
│   ├── api/           # TanStack Mutations/Services
│   └── index.ts       # PUBLIC API: The ONLY entry point for this slice
├── entities/          # [entity-name]/
│   ├── ui/            # Passive UI (UserCard, EntityRow)
│   ├── model/         # Domain state (Zustand), Types
│   └── index.ts       # PUBLIC API
└── shared/            # ui/ (shadcn), api/ (apiClient), lib/ (utils)
3. Strict Implementation Rules
Public API (index.ts): Every slice must have an index.ts. You are STRICTLY FORBIDDEN from importing deep files.

Bad: import { UserCard } from '@/entities/user/ui/UserCard'

Good: import { UserCard } from '@/entities/user'

No Cross-Importing: Slices in the same layer cannot import from each other (e.g., features/login cannot import from features/register). Move shared logic down to entities or shared.

SRP (Single Responsibility): Logic (hooks/api) must be in model/api segments, while UI remains in the ui segment.

4. Technical Stack & CMS Patterns
Data Fetching: Use TanStack Query. Queries go in entities/[name]/api, Mutations go in features/[name]/api.

State Management:

Global/Domain State: Zustand (placed in entities/[name]/model).

Local UI State: useState.

Tables/Forms:

Tables: @tanstack/react-table in widgets.

Forms: react-hook-form + zod in features.

UI Components: Use shadcn/ui. Core atoms belong in shared/ui.

5. Dual Theme & Aesthetic Standards
Semantic Tokens: Only use Tailwind classes like bg-background, text-foreground, border-border.

No Hardcoded Colors: Avoid bg-white or text-gray-900. Use bg-card and text-muted-foreground.

Loading States: Every data-driven component must have a Skeleton (shadcn) in its ui segment.

Button Loading: Buttons must show Loader2 and be disabled during isPending.

6. Naming Conventions
Components: PascalCase (e.g., UserTable.tsx).

Hooks: camelCase starting with 'use' (e.g., useUserActions.ts).

Files: Kebab-case for non-component files (e.g., api-client.ts).

Icons: Use lucide-react.

7. Performance & Clean Code
Minimize useEffect. Prefer event-driven updates.

Use early returns for loading/error states.

TypeScript: Strict mode. No any. Use interface for props and type for API responses.